{
  "texts": [
    "Scenario 2 and Scenario 3 were available, since both have winning coalitions.",
    "After a bargaining process that lasted three months, the President chose scenario 3, a coalition on the Right.Disregarding a dimension x of the Ground space amounts, in mathematical terms, to a shift of the ground of p-site a = ( (I, A, (A i))).",
    "Such a transformation is induced by a the projection say p x of A onto B parallel to the disregarded dimension.",
    "The resulting p-site is the G-image of a by p x denoted p x a ≡ ( (I, B, (B i))) where B = p x (A) and B i = p x (A i) (see definition and notation 3.2.2).",
    "◯ Category of P-foundation bpol • [I, ⋅]Objects of this category are p-sites and the morphisms of domain a and codomain b, denoted bpol • [I, ⋅](a, b).The identity on A induces an identity on a."
  ]
}